text: 大约是7月中旬的上午10：00，你刚刚坠毁在南美洲的阿塔卡马沙漠。你的轻型双引擎飞机，包括飞行员和副驾驶的身体，已经完全烧毁，只剩下框架。你们中没有人受伤。飞行员在坠机前无法通知任何人您的位置。然而，他在撞击前曾表示，你距离一个采矿营地50英里，这是最近的已知定居点，距离你飞行计划中的航线大约65英里。除了偶尔的仙人掌外，附近的区域相当平坦，看起来相当贫瘠。上次天气报告显示，今天的温度将达到 110 华氏度，这意味着地面温度将达到 130 华氏度。你穿着轻便的衣服——短袖衬衫、裤子、袜子和街头鞋。每个人都有一块手帕，总共有 3 包香烟和一支圆珠笔。在您的飞机起火之前，您的团队能够打捞出“打捞物品”页面上列出的 15 件物品。你的任务是根据它们对你的生存的重要性对这些物品进行排名，从“1”开始表示最重要，到“15”表示最不重要。

Torch with 4 battery-cells
带 4 节电池的火炬
Folding knife 折刀
Air map of the area
该地区的航空地图
Plastic raincoat (large size)
塑料雨衣（大尺寸）
Magnetic compass 磁罗盘
First-aid kit 急救箱
45 calibre pistol (loaded)
45口径手枪（上膛）
Parachute (red & white) 降落伞（红色和白色）
Bottle of 1000 salt tablets
一瓶1000片盐片
2 litres of water per person
每人2升水
A book entitled ‘Desert Animals That Can Be Eaten’
一本名为《可以食用的沙漠动物》的书
Sunglasses (for everyone)
太阳镜（适合所有人）
2 litres of 180 proof liquor
2升180度白酒
Overcoat (for everyone) 大衣（适合所有人）
A cosmetic mirror 化妆品镜子

text: It is approximately 10:00 am in mid-July and you have just crash landed in the Atacama Desert in South America. Your light twin-engined plane containing the bodies of the pilot and co-pilot has completely burned out with only the frame remaining. None of you have been injured. The pilot was unable to notify anyone of your position before the crash. However, he had indicated before impact that you were 50 miles from a mining camp, which is the nearest known settlement, and approximately 65 miles off the course that was filed in your Flight Plan. The immediate area is quite flat, except for occasional cacti, and appears to be rather barren. The last weather report indicated that the temperature would reach 110 F today, which means that the temperature at ground level will be 130 F. You are dressed in lightweight clothing-short-sleeved shirts, pants, socks, and street shoes. Everyone has a handkerchief and collectively, you have 3 packs of cigarettes and a ballpoint pen. Before your plane caught fire, your group was able to salvage the 15 items listed on the “Salvaged Items” page. Your task is to rank these items according to their importance to your survival, starting with a “1” for the most important,to a “15” for the least important.
